The chest inside Lumbridge Castle can be opened during the Lost Tribe quest with a key to obtain a set of H.A.M. robes belonging to Sigmund. After the quest is completed the chest can no longer be opened and any attempt to do so will give the following message in the chat box:

  • You have already found the H.A.M robes in the chest.

Strangely enough, opening the chest during the quest with the intended key changes the apparence and function of the chest to be identical to a chest in the Observatory Dungeon which contains an Antipoison(1). While the player opening the chest with the key will obtain a set of H.A.M. robes instead as intended, any player not doing the quest searching the already opened chest at the same time will indeed get the Antipoison(1) from it.

The '''chest''' inside [[Lumbridge Castle]] can be opened during the [[The Lost Tribe|Lost Tribe]] quest with a [[Key (The Lost Tribe)|key]] to obtain a set of [[H.A.M. robes]] belonging to [[Sigmund]].
After the quest is completed the chest can no longer be opened and any attempt to do so will give the following message in the [[chat box]]:
*You have already found the H.A.M robes in the chest.

Strangely enough, opening the chest '''during the quest''' with the intended [[Key (The Lost Tribe)|key]] changes the apparence and function of the chest to be identical to a [[Chest (Observatory Dungeon, Antipoison)|chest in the Observatory Dungeon]] which contains an [[Antipoison(1)]]. While the player opening the chest with the key will obtain a set of [[H.A.M. robes]] instead as intended, any player '''not doing the quest''' searching the already opened chest at the same time will indeed get the [[Antipoison(1)]] from it.
